{
  "texts": [
    "• Prevention of adverse effect: It is important to prevent adverse effects which occur when the WPP prediction decreases while the actual WPP output increases, causing undesired operations in the power system.",
    "Therefore, more effective metrics need to be developed and utilized to evaluate the WPP performance, taking into account these requirements and other factors in power system operations.",
    "• Wind power ramp consideration: The wind power ramp events possess a great potential of facilitating WPP models to address impacts brought by sudden large wind changes.",
    "Hence, it is of great practical value to study WPP methods together with better utilizing the historical wind power ramp pattern and with integrating more effective wind power ramp predictions.",
    "Overall, these requirements highlight the need for more research in developing effective WPP methods and metrics that can meet the diverse needs of power grid operations."
  ]
}